/-
PROBLEM
Given sequences with summable L¹ telescoping bounds, convergence holds a.e.

PROVIDED SOLUTION
The proof uses the monotone convergence theorem / Fubini.

1. Since h_sum says ∑ ∫ |u k - u(k+1)| < ∞, we have ∫ (∑ |u k - u(k+1)|) < ∞ by lintegral_tsum or integral_tsum (swapping sum and integral for non-negative integrands).
2. Therefore ∑ |u k ω - u(k+1) ω| < ∞ for a.e. ω.
3. When this series converges, u n ω is Cauchy (absolutely summable telescoping series), hence convergent in ℝ (which is complete).

Use ae_of_integral_tsum_lt or similar. The key Mathlib lemma might be: if ∑ ∫ |fₖ| < ∞ (with each fₖ integrable), then ∑ |fₖ(ω)| < ∞ a.e.
-/
lemma ae_tendsto_of_summable_l1_diff {P : Measure α} [IsProbabilityMeasure P]
    {u : ℕ → α → ℝ} (hu_meas : ∀ n, Measurable (u n))
    (hu_bdd : ∀ n ω, 0 ≤ u n ω ∧ u n ω ≤ 1)
    (h_sum : Summable (fun k => ∫ ω, |u k ω - u (k + 1) ω| ∂P)) :
    ∀ᵐ ω ∂P, ∃ l, Tendsto (u · ω) atTop (nhds l) := by
  -- By Fubini's theorem, since the series of integrals converges, the series of functions converges almost everywhere.
  have h_ae_conv : ∀ᵐ ω ∂P, Summable (fun k => |u k ω - u (k + 1) ω|) := by
    have h_ae_conv : ∫⁻ ω, ∑' k, ENNReal.ofReal |u k ω - u (k + 1) ω| ∂P < ⊤ := by
      rw [ MeasureTheory.lintegral_tsum ];
      · refine' lt_of_le_of_lt ( ENNReal.tsum_le_tsum fun n => _ ) _;
        use fun n => ENNReal.ofReal ( ∫ ω, |u n ω - u ( n + 1 ) ω| ∂P );
        · rw [ MeasureTheory.ofReal_integral_eq_lintegral_ofReal ];
          · refine' MeasureTheory.Integrable.abs _;
            refine' MeasureTheory.Integrable.sub _ _ <;> refine' MeasureTheory.Integrable.mono' _ _ _ <;> norm_num [ hu_meas, hu_bdd ];
            exacts [ fun _ => 1, MeasureTheory.integrable_const _, hu_meas n |> Measurable.aestronglyMeasurable, Filter.Eventually.of_forall fun _ => abs_le.mpr ⟨ by linarith [ hu_bdd n ‹_› ], by linarith [ hu_bdd n ‹_› ] ⟩, fun _ => 1, MeasureTheory.integrable_const _, hu_meas ( n + 1 ) |> Measurable.aestronglyMeasurable, Filter.Eventually.of_forall fun _ => abs_le.mpr ⟨ by linarith [ hu_bdd ( n + 1 ) ‹_› ], by linarith [ hu_bdd ( n + 1 ) ‹_› ] ⟩ ];
          · exact Filter.Eventually.of_forall fun ω => abs_nonneg _;
        · exact?;
      · exact fun n => ( ENNReal.measurable_ofReal.comp_aemeasurable ( Measurable.aemeasurable ( by measurability ) ) );
    have h_ae_conv : ∀ᵐ ω ∂P, ∑' k, ENNReal.ofReal |u k ω - u (k + 1) ω| < ⊤ := by
      exact MeasureTheory.ae_lt_top ( by measurability ) h_ae_conv.ne;
    filter_upwards [ h_ae_conv ] with ω hω using by rw [ ← summable_norm_iff ] ; exact ( by simpa [ ENNReal.ofReal ] using ENNReal.summable_toReal ( ne_of_lt hω ) ) ;
  filter_upwards [ h_ae_conv ] with ω hω using cauchySeq_tendsto_of_complete ( show CauchySeq fun n => u n ω from by
                                                                                exact? )

